I agree with the conclusion that a claim of conformance includes a claim that equivalents are valid. 
I think that in fact there is only ever a claim for this - there is no test by which it can be absolutely determined that a given "candidate equivalent" in Eric's terminology is in fact valid, just an assertion that it is sufficient. 
